Using a standard

   while($cursor->hasNext()) {
     $cursor->getNext();
   }

loop I'm running into an issue on some queries where there should be (for example) 152 results but I'm getting 153 back instead with the last getNext() returning null. I can take the same exact query executed in PHP and paste it into the mongo console and it returns 152 results, but PHP will allow that loop to run 153 times with the last one being null.

Obviously null isn't a valid result and hasNext() should have returned false if the next call to getNext() wasn't a real object.

This doesn't happen with all queries -- just some. I can't seem to pin it down but I'll continue to try.

Until then I was wondering if taking a gander at the PHP mongo module could reveal a reason why this may be happening? I'll also do some research in the module as well.

